#  Turn GOV.UK Account on and off

You can turn GOV.UK Account on and off. When you turn off GOV.UK Account, the following happens with immediate effect:

- new users are not be able to sign up for GOV.UK Account
- existing users can no longer access their accounts or the data stored in their accounts
- all sign in attempts are redirected to an error page

## Deciding to turn off GOV.UK Account

You may need to turn off GOV.UK Account because of a:

- security incident or data leak
- major breaking bug
- request from the senior management team (SMT)

